node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YOLOMETIMES HAVE TO LET THE SAME PERSON GO OF MANY DIFFERENT TIMES.'.

node.text:
Letting go is a practice and something you have to do continually. 

Healing is like waves— some days you’ll be fine, others you’ll be stuck spiraling and recycling the same thoughts and feelings not knowing what to do with them. Healing and letting go doesn’t happen once, it happens over and over again. Its in your choices, and behaviors. The thoughts you choose to give meaning and the ones you challenge.  Don’t be discouraged or think that whatever you’re doing isn’t working. Give yourself time and be patient.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 12, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'BE PREPARED TO LOSE SOME PEOPLE WHEN YOU CHOOSE YOURSELF 1 1990'.

node.text:
It sucks that sometimes it gotta be like that. That’s why it’s so much easier to choose others Bc we don’t want to risk the loss of connection (even when it’s not the healthiest)

But remember that any connection that exists based on you not choosing yourself and prioritizing your own growth may not be as meaningful as you think  Some relationships only last when you consistently put yourself last. Don’t be afraid of the solitude that might come with your decision.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 10, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Some people won't be able to love you the way you wanted them to, don't hate them for it. 4654 OUTFRONT'.

node.text:
Some people cannot be who you wished or wanted them to be, and that is ok. 

Love is a complicated and complex thing.  Everyone shows their love in different ways and languages. How you feel loved may be completely opposite to how someone you love feels loved. The way we express that love differes and depends on our unique and individual experiences. If you can remember that love should not be contingent on whether someone loves you back you can create peace and harmony. Practice radical acceptance. Accept who people are even if it means they’re not compatible with your type of live, you can experience others as they are rather than evaluating and judging their flaws or differences.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'STOP EXPECTING EVERYONE To HAVE THE SAME HEART AS YOU DO.'.

node.text:
Some people’s love will not match yours. They won’t be able to love like you do, and may not be compatible with how you like to feel loved, don’t hate them for it. We all have a different capacity for how much love we can have for others, and ourselves.

Don’t let someone’s inability to love you discourage you from how much you’re able to love. We all have different hearts, some are more tortured than others. Having a big heart is something to love about yourself. Tag someone who may need the love today. 🤍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'LETTING GO WILL MEAN CONTINUALLY CHOOSING YOURSELF IN THE MOMENTS YOU WANT TO CHOOSE THEM'.

node.text:
Letting go is an act of self love. Self love is actively choosing yourself over and over and over again. Especially in the times when you don’t really want to. 

Insert anything for the word “them” it could be, booze, friendships, family, a certain situation. Etc. There will be times where you want to self abandon. There will be moments when you want to leave yourself and revisit old behaviors. There will be times where you want to stop choosing yourself. 

There will be temptations, things that you interpret as signs or things you give meaning to that will distract you. Remember you are not your feelings. You’re not your emotions and you’re not your thoughts. Learn to separate from them and stay grounded.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'DON'T DOUBT YOUR WORTH JUST BECAUSE SOMEONE COULDN'T SEEIT'.

node.text:
What are you doubting your self worth for???? Because you stood up for yourself for once?? Set a boundary? Finally chose yourself? Stopped people pleasing? Raised your standards? 

Don’t let anyone make you question yourself for making some hard but needed choices. Don’t let people who don’t value you determine how much you value yourself. Your self worth must remain the same despite what anyone thinks of you or how others treat you. Remember their behavior is a reflection of them, NOT you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on September 02, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Love yourself so you don' lose yourselfin people who don' love you. PUP'.

node.text:
Love yourself so you learn to choose the right people for you. 

It’s easier to lose yourself in others as a way to avoid loving yourself. It’s easier to love someone than it is to love yourself. It’s easier to choose someone over choosing yourself. Love yourself so you know the type of love you need. Love yourself so you know when to let go and walk away. Love yourself so you know what it takes for you to not self abandon and leave yourself for someone else. Do the hard work, No one is saying it’s easy. The work means different choices, new behaviors, not falling into old patterns, habits and ways of thinking. It’s time to get uncomfortable. If you don’t know what it takes to love you, how will someone  else?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 31, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, brick wall and text that says 'RIGHT PERSON FOR SOMEONE SOMETIMES YOU'LL BE THE WHO IS NOT RIGHT PERSON. READY FOR THE TFW OI AP'.

node.text:
Sometimes you’ll have to let go of what’s not meant for you. You’ll have to accept the truth and know when it’s time to walk away. 

Sometimes you’ll have to redirect all the love you have back to yourself. You’ll have to understand that it’s not always you. Sometimes you’ll learn the hard way, that some people are teaching you how to live yourself by choosing yourself. Sometimes it won’t work out, the more you can accept and be open to discomfort and change the more you’ll see it as an opportunity to grow and heal parts of you that seek out one sided love.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 29, 2021. May be an image of ‎outdoors and ‎text that says '‎AT SOME POINT, YOU'LL HAVE TO REALIZE THAT SOME PEOPLE WON'T BE READY FOR YOUR LOVE. REGENCY بر‎'‎‎.

node.text:
Some people won’t be ready for what you have to offer. Don’t hate them for it. 

Love them through it (at a distance if you need to) people don’t have to choose you, they have to choose themselves first. They have to first believe they are worthy of love. You can spend years chasing, convincing and trying to make someone see your worth. Or you can know it in your heart and be ok with letting them go. Not everyone will be ready for the love you have to give.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 26, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and brick wall.

node.text:
Whatever it is that you’re forcing rn— let it go. 

Good things don’t need to be forced. Things that are meant to be feel happen naturally. Anything that is costing you your peace, excessive effort or too much compromise is telling you something. You won’t have to force what’s meant for you or easily maintained. If you feel like you’re giving way more than you have in order to keep someone’s interest it’s going to cost you later. Let go. Let it be:

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 24, 2021. May be an image of sky, road and text that says 'Don't be surprised when choosing yourself means the end of certain conNec ions.'.

node.text:
Good morning, don’t be surprised. 

Choosing yourself will have consequences. It will end connections you thought would have never ended. That will make you doubt your choice. It will make you question “am I really worth choosing me or am I being extra?” You’re not being extra- choosing yourself will feel mean if you’ve never done it. So will setting boundaries. The more you begin to do this, the more you’ll start to believe in your own worth and attract people who do too.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 21, 2021.

node.text:
There’s a difference between asking for what you need and asking someone who is incapable of meeting your needs. When we ask the wrong person it can become very easy to assume that we are the problem. That we are too “needy“ and this is a major reason why it’s sometimes easier not to speak up or to pretend like you don’t have actual needs. 

Remember that someone who is not emotionally available, someone who isn’t in tune with their own needs, boundaries and emotions is likely not going to be able to understand yours. Let alone meet them. When you ask the wrong person you feel doubt, insecurity unsure of yourself— the best relationships encompass the opposite of that. Security, assurance and love. People who get you and understand you don’t promote those types of feelings. Make sure you’re speaking up for yourself but also make sure you’re not just asking the wrong person.
